{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a8a2df8d-f8c4-4095-a2ed-ccca93454dbf","content":"In .NET 10, Android's `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` is fully removed. The replacement is the **WindowInsets API**. Here's how to handle it in MAUI:\n\n**Option 1 — Use `AdjustPan` (simplest)**\n\nIn `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:\n```csharp\n[Activity(..., WindowSoftInputMode = SoftInput.AdjustPan)]\npublic class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity { }\n```\n\nThis scrolls the whole view up but may hide your header/toolbar.\n\n**Option 2 — Use WindowInsets (recommended for chat UIs)**\n\nAdd a listener that adjusts bottom padding when the keyboard appears:\n\n```csharp\n// Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs\nusing AndroidX.Core.View;\n\nprotected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)\n{\n    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);\n\n    var content = FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content)!;\n    ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(content, new KeyboardInsetsListener());\n}\n\nclass KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener\n{\n    public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)\n    {\n        var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());\n        var navInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());\n        var bottom = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navInsets.Bottom);\n        v.SetPadding(v.PaddingLeft, v.PaddingTop, v.PaddingRight, bottom);\n        return insets;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**iOS** generally handles this automatically, but if needed, subscribe to `UIKeyboard.WillShowNotification` and adjust your layout's bottom margin.\n\n**Layout tip** — structure your chat page so the input bar is pinned to the bottom of a `Grid`:\n\n```xml\n<Grid RowDefinitions=\"*,Auto\">\n    <CollectionView Grid.Row=\"0\" ItemsSource=\"{Binding Messages}\" />\n    <HorizontalStackLayout Grid.Row=\"1\" Padding=\"8\">\n        <Entry Placeholder=\"Message...\" HorizontalOptions=\"FillAndExpand\" />\n        <Button Text=\"Send\" />\n    </HorizontalStackLayout>\n</Grid>\n```\n\nOption 2 gives you the best chat-app UX — the input bar slides up while the message list stays scrollable above it.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4bc8e6ed-5a42-40ec-a193-05e6d5e94e0e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a .NET MAUI issue where the keyboard covers the text input at the bottom of the screen. They mention that `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` worked in .NET 9 but doesn't work in .NET 10. Let me provide guidance on how to handle this in .NET 10.\n\nIn .NET MAUI (.NET 8+), the `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` was already deprecated on Android because Google deprecated the `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` flag in Android 11 (API 30). The recommended approach changed over time.\n\n\nFor .NET 10, I should focus on the current best practices—either using `AdjustPan` mode or manually handling keyboard insets with the edge-to-edge display approach that respects system insets. I should use the `Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.AndroidSpecific` namespace with `AdjustPan` mode as a fallback, and for the modern approach in .NET 10, leverage the `WindowInsets` API to listen for keyboard visibility changes and adjust the view's padding dynamically.\n\nSetting up a listener that responds to IME insets...","outputTokens":1600,"requestId":"9814:34C090:1C48C17:1F48924:6A05212E"},"id":"56631999-69bc-43ce-b95d-33c285717378","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:11:39.480Z","parentId":"dc92e6a0-3b8f-4032-8b28-aa64e977ee58"}
